
1. How do you read only specific columns from a Google Sheet in Colab?

	Use usecols parameter in pd.read_csv() after mounting Google Drive:

python
import pandas as pd
from google.colab import drive
drive.mount('/content/drive')

# Read ONLY specific columns (by name or position)
url = 'https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/YOUR_SHEET_ID/export?format=csv'
df = pd.read_csv(url, usecols=['Name', 'Sales', 'Date'])  # By column names
# OR usecols=[0,2,4] for columns A,C,E

